From a6e2c180b45157ec9409ff993e9916602a41caad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Emergent Agent <agent@emergent.sh>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 21:42:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Disable expo-updates channel for v1.0 TestFlight (fixes
 StartupProcedure crash)

Symbolicated crash on build 3 showed:
  StartupProcedure.throwException(_:)
  ErrorRecovery.tryRelaunchFromCache()

Root cause: eas.json had 'channel' set on testflight + production profiles,
which causes EAS to auto-inject the EXUpdates native module into the iOS
binary. But app.json never configured expo.updates.url / runtimeVersion /
the expo-updates plugin, and expo-updates is not in node_modules.

At startup, EXUpdates queries u.expo.dev for a matching update, fails to
find one, falls into ErrorRecovery.tryRelaunchFromCache, cache is empty,
embedded fallback metadata absent => throws unhandled NSException => SIGABRT.

Removing 'channel' from testflight + production tells EAS to skip
expo-updates entirely. App runs purely from the embedded JS bundle, no
startup network query, no error recovery path triggered.

OTA updates can be added properly later by installing expo-updates,
configuring app.json with updates.url + runtimeVersion + plugin, then
re-adding channels here.
---
 frontend/eas.json | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

